RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 1 5F Turf CR: 81. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 28000. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-w inners Of A Race Since July 5 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000. Minnesota Bred Claiming Price $25,000. RACE.FOOTNOTES: THUNDERS ROCKNROLL was quick to begin from the outside to cross over to the rail early on, challenged through the upper stretch and kicked on gamely to be clear late under strong handling. MORGS WORLD was hustled along early while racing off the early pace, swung five to six wide into the upper stretch and kept on gamely to the wire. CALY BALI was off slowly, lost a considerable amount of ground at the start, rushed up two deep to challenge the early leader from the outside and weakened in the final stages. CAJUN NINJA coaxed along early, raced two deep past the three eighths pole, angled five deep through the stretch run and raced evenly late with no closing run. HEATIN UP was forwardly placed to lay up close early, raced near the rail through the far turn and faded. WEST SIDE GIRL was void of early speed, raced far back and trailed.
